Browser Fingerprinting is scary, you can have any single security control implemented and believe to be impenetrable, and only one backdoor in one advertising website can see your search/browser history.
In context of a corporation, perhaps a browser fingerprint to a corporate c-suite level executive and either their work or personal browser fingerprint could reveal to those who don't need to know the ability to decipher liklihood of a contract or decision based 
on that c-suite person's websites visited. 
